Use logical-line cursor commands in `keybindings.json`:

```json
[
  {
    "key": "ctrl+alt+down",
    "command": "editor.action.insertCursorBelow",
    "args": { "logicalLine": true }
  },
  {
    "key": "ctrl+alt+up",
    "command": "editor.action.insertCursorAbove",
    "args": { "logicalLine": true }
  }
]
```

This makes cursor addition move between actual document lines, skipping wrapped visual segments—the behavior shown in the preferred GIF.
